    "excerpt": "This Chinese translation of an Ashkenazi nusaḥ for the piyyut \"Shokhen Ad\" following Nishmat Kol Ḥai is found on page 3 of the liner notes for the Chinese edition of Richard Collis's album <a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/?p=46233\"><em>We Sing We Stay Together: Shabbat Morning Service Prayers</em> (Wǒmen gēchàng, wǒmen xiāngjù — Ānxírì chén dǎo qídǎo)</a>. . . .",
    "content": "\n<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" class=\"draggable toggleable-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th id=\"x\" style=\"text-align: right;\">Source (Hebrew)</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Translation (Chinese)</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"he\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nשׁוֹכֵן עַד מָּרוֹם וְקָּדוֹשׁ שְׁמוֹ. וְכָתוּב:<br />\nרַנְּנוּ צַדִּיקִים בַּיהוה,<br />\nלַיְשָׁרִים נָאוָה תְהִלָּה. <span class=\"citation\">(תהלים לג:א)</span>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"chinese\" lang=\"zh\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n祂永存，祂的名尊贵而圣洁。经载：<br />\n(你）Hashem的义人，欢乐地歌唱，<br />\n(因为）义人应当歌颂（祂）。\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"he\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבְּפִי <span class=\"acrostic\">יְ</span>שָׁרִים תִּתְהַלָּל<br />\nוּבְשִׂפְתֵי <span class=\"acrostic\">צַ</span>דִּיקִים תִּתְבָּרַךְ<br />\nוּבִלְשׁוֹן <span class=\"acrostic\">חֲ</span>סִידִים תִּתְרוֹמָם<br />\nוּבְקֶרֶב <span class=\"acrostic\">קְ</span>דוֹשִׁים תִּתְקַדָּשׁ\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"chinese\" lang=\"zh\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n借着虔诚信徒的舌头，你将被颂扬； <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\n在圣民中，你将被圣化。<span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\n借着虔诚信徒的舌头，你将被颂扬； <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\n在圣民中，你将被圣化。 <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<hr />\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<hr />\n<p>This Chinese translation of an Ashkenazi nusaḥ for the piyyut &#8220;Shokhen Ad&#8221; following Nishmat Kol Ḥai is found on page 3 of the liner notes for the Chinese edition of Richard Collis&#8217;s album <a href=\"/?p=46233\"><em>We Sing We Stay Together: Shabbat Morning Service Prayers</em> (Wǒmen gēchàng, wǒmen xiāngjù — Ānxírì chén dǎo qídǎo)</a>.</p>\n<h3>Source(s)</h3>\n<style type=\"t